-- Hong Kong shares edge up 0.1 pct in half-day session
-- 
-- Tue Dec 23, 2014 11:40PM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Dec 24 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares finished marginally higher on Wednesday in a short trading session, as the stock exchange closed early for the Christmas holiday and will not reopen until Monday.

The Hang Seng index <.HSI> rose 0.1 percent, to 23,349.34, while the China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> lost 1.0 percent, to 11,558.02 points.Among the most actively traded stocks on Hong Kong's main board were ICBC <1398.HK>, down 1.3 percent to HK$5.46  CCT Land <0261.HK>, unchanged at HK$0.02 and Bank of China <3988.HK>, down 0.7 percent to HK$4.21. Chinese investment flowing from Shanghai into Hong Kong through the mutual market access pilot programme took up 0.28 billion yuan of the 10.5 billion yuan daily quota <.SQUOTA.HS>. Total trading volume of companies included in the HSI index was 0.7 billion shares.  Keywords: MARKETS HONGKONG STOCKS/CLOSE